{"article_id":"1f21qHvBDZa9SDHj","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The House approved a nine-month funding bill for the Department of Homeland Security Tuesday ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"breaking a lengthy stalemate over President Barack Obama ' s immigration policies","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"that exacerbated the rift between Speaker John Boehner and the conservative wing of his conference .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"The measure passed 257-167 ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"with 182 Democrats and 75 Republicans voting","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"to beat a Friday midnight deadline","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"for DHS funding to expire .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Voting against the measure were 167 Republicans , many in protest to the lack of language","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"to block Obama ' s immigration policies .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"The vote ends a three-month battle over Obama ' s decision","depth":4},{"id":10,"text":"to use executive powers","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"to shield nearly 5 million immigrants from deportation , a move","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"that enraged congressional Republicans .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Boehner was only able to avoid a government shutdown last Friday","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"after backroom negotiations with House Democrats led to a vote on a \" clean \" funding bill this week .","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"\" After bringing our Homeland Security to the brink of a shutdown ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"I ' m glad","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"Republicans have finally realized the futility","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"in refusing to protect the American people , \"","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"Rep. Joe Crowley","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"( D-N.Y. ) ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"the vice chairman of the Democratic caucus .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"\" Picking a fight with President Obama","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"and jeopardizing the safety of American families was not only absurd ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"but it was downright dangerous . \"","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"The Senate has already approved a bill","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"to extend DHS funding through September ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"so the legislation now heads to Obama ' s desk","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"to be signed .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"Boehner","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"( R-Ohio )","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"was forced to use an obscure procedural rule","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"to reverse an earlier vote against a clean bill ,","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"after the House and Senate were unable to forge an agreement","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"to enter conference negotiations","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"before DHS funding expires .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"The vote allows the House to reverses its position","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"of disagreeing with the Senate ' s legislation .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"When announcing his plan to Republicans Tuesday morning ,","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Boehner told GOP House members","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"his decision","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"to allow a clean funding bill to come to the House floor","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"was \" the right one for this team , and the right one for this country . \"","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"\" I am as outraged and frustrated as you at the lawless and unconstitutional actions of this president , \"","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Boehner said .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Boehner received a standing ovation ,","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"according to a source in the room .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"The speaker ' s decision","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"to allow a vote","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"showed","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"he is refusing to continue to be hamstrung on the DHS issue by a pocket of conservatives .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"Indeed , he invited their wrath","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"by working with Democrats","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"to fund the anti-terrorism agency through the remainder of the fiscal year , Sept. 30 .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"The stalemate emerged out of Obama ' s November unilateral action","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"to shield millions of undocumented immigrants from deportation .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"The House tried to gut those provisions ,","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"but the Senate was not able to get a matching bill through the chamber .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"Congress last week passed legislation","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"to fund DHS through Friday .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"Boehner told the gathering of Republicans","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"that another short-term bill would not pass the House","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"and said","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"that Senate Republicans \" never found a way","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"to win this fight . \"","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"\" The three-week CR","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"we offered","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"would have kept this fight going","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"and allowed us to continue to put pressure on Senate Democrats to do the right thing , \"","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"Boehner said in the meeting .","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"\" Unfortunately , that plan was rejected . \"","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"A DHS shutdown ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Boehner said ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"would be dangerous to national security .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"\" With more active threats coming into the homeland ,","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"I don ' t believe","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"that ' s an option , \"","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"\" Imagine","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"if ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"God forbid ,","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"another terrorist attack hits the United States . \"","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"The Senate Monday rejected the House ' s offer","depth":5},{"id":83,"text":"to enter formal conference negotiations between its clean bill and the House ' s legislation ,","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"which attempted to stop President Barack Obama ' s changes to the enforcement of immigration laws .","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"House Republicans are now turning their attention to the courts","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"to oppose Obama ' s executive actions .","depth":5},{"id":87,"text":"A federal judge ruled last month","depth":4},{"id":88,"text":"that Obama did not have the authority","depth":5},{"id":89,"text":"to halt the deportations .","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"The administration quickly appealed ,","depth":3},{"id":91,"text":"but several conservatives said Tuesday","depth":4},{"id":92,"text":"they now see the courts as the most effective way","depth":5},{"id":93,"text":"to halt the immigration policies .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":187,"left":175,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":106,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":102,"right":105,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":96,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":0,"right":95,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":99,"right":100,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":99,"left":3,"right":98,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":4,"right":97,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":9,"right":104,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":10,"right":103,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":130